our]]''\n| Fitz\n| Episode: \"The Ass\"\n|-\n| {{nowrap|2018\u20132019}}\n| ''[[Wyatt Cenac's Problem Areas]]''\n| {{n/a|none}}\n| 20 episodes; executive producer\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}} \n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series|Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety, Music or Comedy Series]]\n| rowspan=\"6\"|''[[The Daily Show|The Daily Show with Jon Stewart]]''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Emmys\">{{cite web|title=John Oliver|url=http://www.emmys.com/bios/john-oliver|website=emmys.com|publisher=Television Academy|access-date=26 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317135550/http://www.emmys.com/bios/john-oliver|archive-date=17 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2009\n| [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: Comedy-Variety Talk Series|Writers Guild of America Award for Comedy/Variety (Including Talk) \u2013 Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=2009 Writers Guild Awards Television, Radio, News, Promotional Writing, and Graphic Animation Nominees Announced|url=http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=3410|access-date=26 February 2016|publisher=The Writers Guild of America|date=8 December 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081212052838/http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=3410|archivedate=12 December 2008}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series|Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety, Music or Comedy Series]]\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Emmys\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2010\n| [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: Comedy-Variety Talk Series|Writers Guild of America Award for Comedy/Variety (Including Talk) \u2013 Series]]\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-a