woodreporter.com/live-feed/fleabag-dominates-tv-critics-awards-1229076 |title='Fleabag' Dominates TV Critics Awards |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |date=3 August 2019 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=5 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Variety Talk Series]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Emmys\" />\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Interactive Program]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[45th People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Award for The Nighttime Talk Show of 2019]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/e-peoples-choice-awards-finalists-complete-list-1202710461/|title=E! People's Choice Awards Finalists Announced; Voting Open Through Oct. 18 \u2013 Complete List|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Greg|last=Evans|date=4 September 2019|accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|2020\n| [[Dorian Awards|Dorian Award for TV Current Affairs Show of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |last1=Beresford |first1=Trilby |title='Parasite,' 'Portrait of a Lady on Fire,' 'Pain and Glory' Lead Dorian Award Nominations |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-gay-lesbian-entertainment-critics-dorian-awards-noms-full-list-1265575 |accessdate=January 6, 2020 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Talk Show]]\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |title=Critics' Choice Awards: 'The Irishman' Leads With 14 Nominations |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-critics-choice-awards-nominations-list-full-1260595/ |accessdate=December 9, 2019 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=December 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Producers Guild of America Awards 2019|Producers Guild of America Award for Outstanding Producer of