er (not the historical figure); do not edit before reading the citation from John Oliver's official website --><ref name=\"bwj\" /> (voice)\n| Episode: \"[[Pay Pal (The Simpsons)|Pay Pal]]\"\n|-\n| ''[[Robot Chicken]]''\n| [[Serpentor]], British Gentleman (voice)\n| Episode: \"G.I. Jogurt\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Comedians in Cars Getting Coffee]]''\n| Himself (guest)\n| Episode: What Kind of Human Animal Would Do This?\n|-\n| 2016\u20132017\n| ''[[Danger Mouse (2015 TV series)|Danger Mouse]]''\n| Augustus P. Crumhorn IV (voice)\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2017\n| ''[[Bob's Burgers]]''\n| Ian (voice)\n| Episode: \"There's No Business Like Mr. Business Business\"\n|-\n| ''[[The Detour (TV series)|The Detour]]''\n| Fitz\n| Episode: \"The Ass\"\n|-\n| {{nowrap|2018\u20132019}}\n| ''[[Wyatt Cenac's Problem Areas]]''\n| {{n/a|none}}\n| 20 episodes; executive producer\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}} \n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series|Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety, Music or Comedy Series]]\n| rowspan=\"6\"|''[[The Daily Show|The Daily Show with Jon Stewart]]''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Emmys\">{{cite web|title=John Oliver|url=http://www.emmys.com/bios/john-oliver|website=emmys.com|publisher=Television Academy|access-date=26 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317135550/http://www.emmys.com/bios/john-oliver|archive-date=17 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2009\n| [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: Comedy-Variety Talk Series|Writers Guild of America Award for Comedy/Variety (Including Talk) \u2013 Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=2009 Writers Guild Awards Television, Radio, News, Promotional Writing, and Graphic Animation Nominees Announced|url=http://www.wga.or